  "body": "# Outdated EIP2333 version\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nA few months ago, EIP 2333 was updated so that `hkdf_mod_r` matched the `KeyGen` function update in the BLS specs. Prysm is still using the old version.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nTry run the EIP's tests against your implementation.\r\n\r\n## The fix\r\nUpdate `hkdf_mod_r` to the new version with the while loop as per [EIP2333](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2333#key-derivation) and run it against the given test vectors:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n1. salt = \"BLS-SIG-KEYGEN-SALT-\"\r\n2. SK = 0\r\n3. while SK == 0:\r\n4.     salt = H(salt)\r\n5.     PRK = HKDF-Extract(salt, IKM || I2OSP(0, 1))\r\n6.     OKM = HKDF-Expand(PRK, key_info || I2OSP(L, 2), L)\r\n7.     SK = OS2IP(OKM) mod r\r\n8. return SK\r\n```",
